pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Memorial Day-More then Just a Mattress Sale</span><hr size=1> Euriped,<br>
I went back and re-read your post 4 times to see if I was missing something. I have to say that your observations were certainly well thought out and articulate. I too believe that indifference may very well be one of the major factors which could destroy our society. I believe that indifference towards those who have bled and died to make our nation what it is, is a disturbing trend in our society. I believe that indifference towards the principles upon which our nation was founded, could certainly wreak havoc on our society. I believe that people who would stand up for freedom of speech, as guaranteed by our Constitution, would seek to keep kids who WANT to pray from doing so in school, could have an adverse effect on our nation. I can't really say whether or not any war actually accomplished what it was set out to, but I can say that to all those who fought, died, and especially those who came home to an INDIFFERENT nation, you are heroes without equal. <br>
   I was in the US Army at the time of the Gulf War.I was just about ready to graduate from AIT when Iraq invaded Kuwait. I won't sit here and pretend that I was thrilled at the prospect of running right over and giving my life, but I can say that I was willing, for that is the job I signed up to do. <br>
   War is the most repugnant thing on the face of the earth. If you study history, you will see that it isn't the warriors who are eager to shed blood, they are mere organs of the state. If in their wisdom the leadership of any nation deems war necessary, warriors have nothing to do but follow orders. Honor, duty, courage, and a love of their nation few who haven't served could possibly know demand nothing less. So I think you might be right, indifference may very well be the root of all evil, but not necessarily the way you think. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uhsianlichen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hsian Li Chen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><FONT COLOR=AA0000><B>Lanys.com Moderator</B></FONT></span><br> <font color=#000033>(5/28/01 11:06:18 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Memorial Day-More then Just a Mattress Sale</span><hr size=1> ok its a holiday and a time to remember your vets all you 'mercans... so play nice.<br>
<br>
its a good topic, one to make you pause and reflect on what those in service have done for you... but lets PLEASE not turn this into a 'military vs. nonmilitary' thing.  <br>
